   NKOREA-FAMINE (United Nations) _ North Korea appears to be
emerging from a prolonged severe famine with the help of
international food aid, but four terrible years of hunger from 1995
through 1998 may have cost the country 2 million to 3 million
lives. Many of the dead were old people and children, or urban
dwellers of any age with no way to forage off the land. By Barbara
Crossette. (The story has moved in ``i'' news file.) 1,300 words.
</P>
