<P>
   SCI-DRUG-RESISTANT-BACTERIA (Washington) _ The CDC reports on
four deaths among previously healthy children, over a period of two
years, from a drug-resistant bacteria. The report is alarming
because these children appear to have acquired their infections not
from hospitals or nursing homes, the only places such cases had
previously occurred, but in their communities. By Sheryl Gay
Stolberg.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CAMPAIGN _ (Moved in ``p'' category) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FORBES-CAMPAIGN (Washington) _ With his second-place finish in
Iowa, Steve Forbes and his operation began crowing about a two-man
race. But how does he follow it up, and where does he go from here?
A look at the challenges he faces and other questions, like whether
he will go negative against Bush and just how much money he has at
the ready. By Frank Bruni. &UR; (BU) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photo is being sent to NYT photo clients.)
</P>
<P>
   DEMS-VALUES (Washington) _ Every few months, small groups of
local Democratic officials journey to special seminars to learn how
to combat a party vulnerability: doubts among voters that the
Democrats embrace mainstream family values. Political strategists
say the public once again sees the Republicans as the party of
values, considering them more trustworthy on a range of moral and
ethical matters like honesty, belief in God, belief in personal
responsibility, and knowing right from wrong. For the Democrats,
this turn of events could not be more frustrating. By Alison
Mitchell. 1,900 words.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photo is being sent to NYT photo clients.)
