</P>
<P>
   PENSION-CASH-BALANCE (Winooski, Vt.)_ Corporate activism did not
come easily to Bill Syverson. But like a lot of his strait-laced
colleagues at IBM, the 49-year-old engineer found his cause this
year after realizing that his employer planned to slash his pension
by what he estimates to be 40 percent. ``It is nothing less than
corporate-sanctioned greed,'' he said. By Richard A. Oppel Jr.
