<HEADLINE>
INGEGNERI JOINS DAILY NEWS AS AD DIRECTOR
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Veteran Arizona advertising executive Paul
Ingegneri has been named advertising director for the Daily News of
Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
   The appointment was announced by Ike Massey, Daily News
president, publisher and CEO.
</P>
<P>
   ``Paul is a quality individual and will be a tremendous asset to
the Daily News,'' Massey said.
</P>
<P>
   Ingegneri spent the past 11 years at Tucson Newspapers, where he
started as an account executive and worked his way up in 1996 to
vice president for advertising. Among the other jobs he held are
classified advertising manager, retail sales manager and new
business development manager.
</P>
<P>
   Tucson Newspapers handles advertising for the Arizona Daily Star
and the Tucson Citizen, which have a combined circulation of about
150,000 daily and 175,000 on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Ingegneri will join the Daily News on August 23.
</P>
<P>
   X X X &QL;
</P>
