<P>
   REL-OVER _ ATLANTA _ The New World was a beacon across the
Atlantic, calling to people looking for a fresh start, sick of the
old ways of the Old World. The Reformation shattered the old
Christendom, but also unleashed new energies, forces that would
sustain a people in a distant land. Protestants translated the
Bible into vernacular languages and encouraged lay learning and
initiative. From Europe, Christian missionaries dispersed to Asia,
Africa _ and the Americas. Their early efforts can still be felt
today. (White, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   REL-IONA _A visit to the Isle of Iona off the NW coast of
Scotland, often called the cradle of Christianity for the northern
British Isles, where abbeys have stood ever since Ireland's St.
Columba sailed here in 563. We describe the natural beauty that has
made the tiny island (pop. 250) a sacred site since Druid times,
talk to visitors on spiritual journeys and describe the work of the
non-denominational Iona Community in humanitarian causes around the
world. (Hulbert, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
