<HEADER>
A4287 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r l BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX     08-20 0527
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WHERE YOU CAN `BUY THAT DREAM'
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: My husband passed away in January of this year. In old
letters, I found mention of a song he liked very much called ``I'll
Buy That Dream.'' I can't remember this song _ can you help?
</P>
<P>
   _ F.N., Weatherford, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: ``I'll Buy That Dream'' was a hit song introduced in the 1945
film ``Sing Your Way Home,'' a wartime high-seas musical starring
Jack Haley and Anne Jeffreys.
</P>
<P>
   The song was a 13-week winner on the ``Lucky Strike Hit Parade''
radio show and was nominated for a best song Oscar, losing to ``It
Might as Well Be Spring'' from ``State Fair.''
</P>
<P>
   Dream was sung by by Anne Jeffreys in the film, and was a hit
for Dick Haymes and Helen Forrest. The 1999 Duke Ellington release
``Duke's Joint'' includes the song, and you can also find it on
``Vol. 1 _ The Very Best of Dick Haymes'' and the ``Hits of '46''
collection.
</P>
<P>
   These lyrics may jog your memory: ``Imagine me with my head on
your shoulder/and you with your lips growing bolder/a sky full of
moon/and a sweet mellow tune/I'll buy that dream.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: With all of the discussion about when the next millennium
begins and the argument that there was no ``year 0,'' when did the
modern Western calendar start? At what point did someone say,
``Well, let's see, Jesus lived 125 years ago, so this is A.D.
126?''
</P>
<P>
   _ R.W., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: That event happened in around A.D. 532, when the Scythian
monk Dionysius Exiguus overhauled the calendar to stop paying
homage to a Roman emperor who persecuted Christians.
</P>
<P>
   In a table indicating when Easter should be celebrated, Exiguus
counted years from the birth of Jesus rather than the reign of
Emperor Diocletian.
</P>
<P>
   His new system had no year 0, skipping from 1 B.C. (''Before
Christ'') to A.D. 1 (''Anno Domini''). The concept of zero as a
number wouldn't be adopted in Europe for another three centuries.
</P>
<P>
   Many scholars believe that Jesus was born between 7 B.C. and 4
B.C., making the Exiguus system inaccurate and the coming year 2000
celebrations several years late.
</P>
<P>
   Q: A friend gave me some self-tanning lotion made by Sun
Laboratories in Beverly Hills, Calif., but couldn't remember where
she got it. Where can I buy it?
</P>
<P>
   _ L.M.L., via the Internet
</P>
<P>
   A: One company that sells Sun Laboratories tanning products is
the Internet retailer SkinSalon.com.
</P>
<P>
   You can order the products online at at www.skinsalon.com or by
mail.
</P>
<P>
   To contact the company for mail-order information, call (818)
790-4885 or write to 2222 Foothill Blvd., Suite E-210, La Canada,
CA 91011-1456.
</P>
<P>
   Sun makes self-tanning sets, exfoliant gels and ``tan
moisturizer maintainers.'' The SkinSalon site also sells Epilyt
Moisturizer, Body Therapeutics sunblock and NeoStrata Exuviance
skin care products.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
