   BUSH-2000 (Akron, Ohio) _ Texas Gov. George W. Bush says he will
still give federal money to faith-based organizations to perform
the social services once provided by the government, even if they
restrict membership to their own believers. The candidate for the
Republican presidential nomination makes the remark at an Akron
born-again Christian agency that once refused a Jew a seat on its
