   GA-TOBACCO _ ATLANTA _ Georgia's struggling tobacco farmers, who
have dealt with reduced growing allotments, diseased crops and
declining cigarette sales, finally get some good news: They will
begin receiving money by December from a settlement with the
tobacco industry. Gov. Roy Barnes appoints a board to oversee
