constructing a Travel page from the package for use by all Cox
papers.
</P>
<P>
   CAYMAN-FALL _ GEORGE TOWN, Cayman Islands_ We needed this family
vacation. Four months of shuffling correspondents throughout the
Eastern Hemisphere to report on the bombing of Yugoslavia and its
aftermath had me in hives at the mere mention of the name
``Milosevic.'' Worse, my family was leaving me notes in lieu of
conversation. To re-connect we went to the Cayman Islands. As it
turns out, this gorgeous three-island chain may be one of the best
kept secrets for family vacations in the Caribbean off-season ?
generally the summer and early fall. Flights, car rentals and rooms
are more reasonable. Restaurants run the gamut: from expensive to
affordable, from authentic island cuisine to Pizza Hut. The primary
entertainment (read that, the beach) is free. And there are a few
things you can't put a price on: No theme park crowds. No
panhandlers. A low crime rate. (Christie, Cox News Service). WITH
PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: This is the same story as CAYMAN-SUMMER with a fall twist.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moved Mon., Aug. 16, in (i) International and (t) Travel
categories.
</P>
<P>
   CAYMAN-TRAVEL _ GEORGE TOWN, Cayman Islands _ Divers.
Honeymooners. Families. Encircled in powdery white beaches that
seem to float calmly in clear
</P>
<P>
   turquoise blue waters, the three islands that make up this
Caribbean chain _ Grand Cayman, Little Cayman and Cayman Brac _
have been expanding in the type of
</P>
<P>
   tourist they attract. For many of the same reasons. This tiny
group of islands has always seemed to hold a special place in the
heart of some wayward group _ from the adventurers who made them a
regular stop to load up on turtle meat, to the pirates rumored to
favor the coves of the sparsely populated islands, to the divers
who have made the Caymans one of the world's top diving
destinations. (Christie, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   CAYMAN-BOX _ An If-You-Go ... With Kids box: Getting there;
getting around; getting going; and getting food. (Christie, Cox
News Service). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moved Mon., Aug. 16, in International and Travel
categories.
</P>
