a no-holds-barred psychological analysis. Giuliani created ``Live
From City Hall'' as a means of talking to ordinary citizens about
the frustrations of city life, and sure enough, he helps dozens of
callers navigate city bureaucracy, foil corrupt landlords and find
jobs. Each Friday morning, Giuliani uses his free air time to
lecture New Yorkers about their supposed bad habits, inveigh
against their collective dysfunction, and exhort them to be more
exemplary human beings, for crying out loud. Although he does solve
many callers' problems, Giuliani often sounds more like a bullying
therapist on the show than an elected official. By Amy Goodnough.
