<P>
   TURKEY-QUAKE (Istanbul, Turkey) _ As the death toll from this
week's earthquake rises, relief workers and government officials in
Turkey say that their most urgent challenge now is preventing the
outbreak of epidemic diseases. The exact number of victims _ dead,
injured and still missing _ from the earthquake is impossible to
determine with precision in the chaos of a city and country
unprepared for such massive destruction. The official crisis center
announced that more than 10,000 bodies have been recovered so far,
and the number of injured has risen to 34,000. By Stephen Kinzer.
