David in Oceanside called recently to complain about the ban on pet
ferrets, the mayor leaned into the microphone on his desk and said,
``There is something deranged about you.'' The mayor created ``Live
From City Hall with Rudy Giuliani'' in 1994 as a means of talking
to ordinary citizens about the frustrations of city life, and sure
enough, he helps dozens of callers navigate city bureaucracy. But
the show is turning out to be as much about trouble-making as
trouble-shooting. By Abby Goodnough. (Scheduled to move by 8:30
