<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Saturday, Aug. 21. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
ILLEGALS (Chandler, Ariz.) - In what may be an unprecedented legal
switcharoo, nearly 30 illegal workers are suing a Chandler print
shop, alleging a pattern of persistent verbal and sexual
harassment. Though they are not in this country legally to work,
they have filed a lawsuit against their former employer over the
harassment, as well as the owners failure to pay them minimum
wages. The federal Equal Employment Opportunity Commission was
expected early Friday to raid the business in its pursuit of the
allegation raised by the undocumented workers. By JIM WALSH. Story
will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
POLICE SEX (Mesa, Ariz.) - Veteran Mesa police officer Mark
