<P>
   DROUGHT-WASHINGTON-ART-2TAKES (POMEROY, Wash.) _ The dryland
farmers _ those who farm without benefit of irrigation from the
Columbia River to the Idaho border and the Oregon border straight
up to the Okanogan Valley _ are getting hammered this summer.
Nowhere is the wheat crop worse than in the southeastern pocket of
Washington state, in Garfield, Franklin, Walla Walla and Whitman
counties. It's farming, and bad years are expected. But no one ever
expected things to get this bad.
</P>
